Commuters along the Abuja-Kaduna expressway have been stranded for over two hours, Daily Trust has gathered. Our correspondent gathered that trouble started when police allegedly hit a tanker driver in Rijinna village, some 23kilometers from Kaduna along the highway. An eyewitness who gave his name as Faruk Abdullahi said tanker drivers blocked both sides of the highway to protest the hiting of one of their members allegedly by the police. He said, "We have been stranded for over two hours and help is yet to arrive. I am trying to see if I can manoeuvre my way out and just go back to Kaduna." When contacted, the Police spokesperson in the state, ASP Mukhtar Aliyu, said he would get back to our correspondent with details.  Details later....